<treatment id="5238349049735D0DA971A728E7487FD7" LSID="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B6744ADB-FE0C-4ACE-90FA-0582683FB0FF" httpUri="http://treatment.plazi.org/id/5238349049735D0DA971A728E7487FD7" lastPageNumber="187" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
<subSubSection id="D3A58F50897A22A5B722EA0A5F69D9F4" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="FD9588866857CB5161BA4FB85D28C10A" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
3.2.1. 
<taxonomicName id="B8AE4C82CC8819FC94D9CABF5253970E" LSID="http://zoobank.org/B6744ADB-FE0C-4ACE-90FA-0582683FB0FF" authority="Jin and Che" authorityName="Jin and Che" authorityYear="2022" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Centrocolumna" higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Centrocolumna" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">Centrocolumna Jin and Che</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="D187DDEB5F68B88388E8112C3926FE51" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5A5904D403B0742F6B79FD0464C42CD8" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="note">
<paragraph id="FEE68F51ECFED869E25573EE96534B4C" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0785A6496BD747730F4FED592EFC2B39" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
Both the ML analyses and BI highly support that the clade 
<taxonomicName id="095E4F1DA929112C703ED76EA1088C32" authorityName="Wang &amp; Che" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Symploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Symploce evidens" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="evidens">
<emphasis id="2731298B6C7A2A5BA6CC702B75B5189C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Symploce evidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wang and Che, 2013 plus one unknown species is the sister to the clade of 
<taxonomicName id="FBB4AA6DC625203A3608D82672E89642" authorityName="Caudell" authorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Blattella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Blattella" order="Blattoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7E2D9743C06C2EFC43BCE3BDBB6E42E4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Blattella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName id="3E47317D4FA9F77DFF2D4A43D0A012FF" authorityName="Bey-Bienko" authorityYear="1950" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Episymploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Episymploce" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CAC08EE09D2196620507C1E31BDB09AF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Episymploce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(bs 100%, pp 1.0). Hind margin of subgenital plate with an obvious protrusion and with the right stylus located on it make them obviously distinguishable from other related genera. Therefore, we establish for them and some other taxonomic units the new genus 
<taxonomicName id="1A7351450CEFE5E2D85A972CACFD6CE3" authorityName="Jin and Che" authorityYear="2022" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Centrocolumna" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Centrocolumna" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="25A71CA18E8BF549128C1D68F939779A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Centrocolumna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jin and Che 
<emphasis id="424F323B4032D10AC2AA84C0EF6449D5" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">gen. nov.</emphasis>
and also propose one new species and eight new combinations.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E861C4154BC8A2365922920FD919086F" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="type species">
<paragraph id="7E56519D2113B89E7141206898661459" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="65E5FA6E3098B1D0E88E99E39C2CF1AD" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
<taxonomicName id="B8A91EA0E81260857953EA43B3C7D267" authorityName="Wang &amp; Che" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Symploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Symploce evidens" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="evidens">
<emphasis id="6F0154C7A2E1DEC5B5A6222E1AC6D986" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Symploce evidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wang and Che, 2013, by present designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3E4FF3DA9DE05E8963A75AA83829048C" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="DD52BA6E4ED641BCB214BB5F15575D3B" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B85CA89495A1A45B962297B7D56A5962" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
<emphasis id="0B951D469FD6E7FD4DB10AC56F32C854" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Male.</emphasis>
Tegmina and hindwings fully developed or slightly reduced. Hindwings with RP branched near the middle, M simple and unbranched, CuA curved with 1-4 complete and 0-5 incomplete branches; apical triangle small or absent. Anteroventral margin of front femur usually Type A. Tergal specialization and medial setal tuft always present on T1, T7 and T10. Subgenital plate asymmetrical, hind margin with a prominent protrusion in the middle, and the right stylus arising upon the protrusion. Bases of two styli obtuse, apices tapering.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C22071DDDC2205D3787DC1D393E3B9DF" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="1BE698D31D96BA62B3509FC5D1F02B18" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9D3D1292F8C0DCF9951207EA572C6308" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
<taxonomicName id="40597721B65EC3D926E441749986FBBD" authorityName="Jin and Che" authorityYear="2022" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Centrocolumna" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Centrocolumna" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E2AEFF0FE05255C3D1880FFC2A996068" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Centrocolumna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the combination of the Latin words 
<emphasis id="7B3E05A65C35AD118A35B6F23F5C2A5E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">centr</emphasis>
- and 
<emphasis id="C69FFFFDB114107A19AA6ABD2E5C9913" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">columna</emphasis>
, refers to the right stylus arising upon the protrusion. The gender of 
<taxonomicName id="E1768A344FBF3095C02E9BA189264752" authorityName="Jin and Che" authorityYear="2022" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Centrocolumna" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Centrocolumna" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AB937511FB5C850A32E25DC396C51952" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Centrocolumna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="35F7EEB178637D26A22FEAD3A356B6FC" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="00DAAA63A540DF91311D0ABB3B626157" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9EEF8EAEB87AE1F5A4C65E34C7E40557" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
This genus is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="7749A3E44C61A1CC0B1D1BF53168B0BB" authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Symploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Symploce" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ACFAD8C002F2D3BFE3AE77CA3B9F308F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Symploce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hebard, 1916, but it can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="A50EEABAAF9AB2C58B9E499081A0AA63" authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Symploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Symploce" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1E400AA049E710EF79F796716D3E487D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Symploce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following characters: 1) T10 usually specialized with setal tuft at disk (absent in 
<taxonomicName id="8138E3E08E12785CCB6B797F732B2688" authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Symploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Symploce" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="074658B2A3C5740059280C544E842822" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Symploce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 2) hind margin of subgenital plate with a prominent protrusion (absent in 
<taxonomicName id="B83B85581B09F978DF97E5A2DC0B27D1" authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Symploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Symploce" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A615B3DEBF6B6AC5C77FC731A8664311" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Symploce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F5E1B2986827F69AF9C6F0D27DF1DE93" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" type="notes">
<paragraph id="8812A1181356E78FF88AD8EA7127CCF4" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5151E0192210676A0334FA9679CA0803" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
According to the generic diagnosis of 
<emphasis id="16326E4304F2536B981E1587EA09C11F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">
<taxonomicName id="2303D2A18EC02AC62E594E0E40FB470A" authorityName="Jin and Che" authorityYear="2022" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Centrocolumna" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Centrocolumna" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F26EFC7A407F8421617617618CB5715E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Centrocolumna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov.
</emphasis>
, we transferred the following species of 
<taxonomicName id="1E50CE470E06CE3546B28EE6C080A903" authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Symploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Symploce" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3A9E8A09A086997933DEFF6762D69393" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Symploce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to this genus after our critical examination of the original literature, especially the grouping of species of 
<taxonomicName id="147BF44778A31557D5156C05F1420981" authorityName="Hebard" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Blaberoidea" genus="Symploce" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Symploce" order="Blattodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3A3B27E0206E44493C0902998770C238" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="187">Symploce</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected from Taiwan and Japan in 
<bibRefCitation id="E4CF28FA870D69FFEC82FD3E0BA09310" author="Asahina, S" journalOrPublisher="Japanese Journal of Sanitary Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" pagination="217 - 235" refId="B2" refString="Asahina, S, 1979b. Taxonomic notes on Japanese Blattaria XI. The species of the tribe Ischnopterites, I. Japanese Journal of Sanitary Zoology 30: 217 - 235" title="Taxonomic notes on Japanese Blattaria XI. The species of the tribe Ischnopterites, I." volume="30" year="1979 b">Asahina (1979b)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="387058BF8ECEEEF12EFDAB45295690E0" author="Roth, LM" journalOrPublisher="Entomologica Scandinavica" pageId="0" pageNumber="187" pagination="155 - 163" refId="B43" refString="Roth, LM, 1987. The genus Symploce Hebard. VIII. Species from Taiwan and the Japanese Islands (Dictyoptera: Blattaria, Blattellidae). Entomologica Scandinavica 18: 155 - 163" title="The genus Symploce Hebard. VIII. Species from Taiwan and the Japanese Islands (Dictyoptera: Blattaria, Blattellidae)." volume="18" year="1987">Roth (1987)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
